title: Bedbugs bite into Paris, stoking fears ahead of the Olympics
description: With the Paris Olympics less than a year away, fears that blood-sucking bedbugs could take a bite out of those attending have led to demands for action.

title: French officials fight a bedbug invasion ahead of the Paris Olympics
description: The French government is rolling out a national plan to combat an invasion of bedbugs in the country's cities, just months before the Olympics are set to be held in Paris.

title: Putin marks anniversary of illegal annexation of Ukrainian regions
description: President Vladimir Putin insisted that the residents of four Ukrainian regions that Russia illegally annexed “made their choice — to be with their Fatherland.”

title: French police accused of systemic discrimination in landmark case
description: A landmark hearing was heard by France’s highest administrative authority over accusations of systemic discrimination in identity checks by French police.

title: Russia hosts Taliban for talks on regional threats and says it will keep funding Afghanistan
description: Russia will keep helping Afghanistan on its own and through the U.N. food agency, officials in Moscow said Friday as they hosted Taliban representatives.

title: Former assistant to Sarah Ferguson, Duchess of York, found dead in Dallas apartment
description: Sarah Ferguson, Duchess of York, mourned the death of her former personal assistant Friday, two days after Dallas police announced the arrest of a suspect charged with her murder.
